@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1 class="text-primary fw-bold">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mt-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>
            At <strong>UniBite</strong>, we value your trust and are committed to protecting your privacy.
            This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our food ordering system.
        </p>

        <h4 class="mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>User Account Details:</strong> Name, email, and login credentials.</li>
            <li><strongOrder Information:</strong> Items ordered, quantities, prices, and payment method.</li>
            <li><strong>System Usage Data:</strong> Basic logs to improve performance and user experience.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="mt-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>To process and manage your food orders.</li>
            <li>To provide receipts and order history for your convenience.</li>
            <li>To improve UniBite’s features and ensure smooth operation.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="mt-4">3. Data Protection</h4>
        <p>
            Your data is stored securely and is only accessible to authorized UniBite staff.
            We do not share your personal information with third parties except as required by law.
        </p>

        <h4 class="mt-4">4. User Rights</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>You can update your account details anytime.</li>
            <li>You can request deletion of your account and associated data.</li>
            <li>You can review your order history directly in the system.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="mt-4">5. Contact Us</h4>
        <p>
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us via the
            <a href="#contact">Contact page</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="text-muted mt-4">
            <em>Last updated: January 2026</em>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
